label: FGS221
info_overview:
Remotely Controlled Relay Switch of Fibaro System is designed to operate in a wall switch box or in locations where the control of an electric device (up to 3kW) is needed.
It is also possible to send a signal to any system that is to be integrated with Fibaro system.
info_inclusion: Add Fibaro Switch to the network by pushing three times key no. 1 or push-button B located inside the housing of the device. For toggle switch perform 3 position changes.
info_exclusion: Remove Fibaro Switch from the network by pushing three times key no. 1 or push-button B located inside the housing of the device. For toggle switch perform 3 position changes.
category_description: Any device attached to the wall that controls a binary status of something, for ex. a light switch

parameters.label: Activate / deactivate functions ALL ON / ALL  OFF
parameters.description: Activate / deactivate functions ALL ON / ALL  OFF

options.label: ALL ON is not active ALL OFF is not active
ALL ON is not active ALL OFF active
ALL ON active ALL OFF is not active
ALL ON active, ALL OFF active

parameters.label: Auto off relay after specified time
parameters.description: Auto off relay after specified time
parameters.overview: Auto off relay after specified time, with the possibility of manual override - immediate Off after button push.

options.label: Manual override disabled
options.overview: After single button push the relay turns on and automatically turns off after specified time.

options.label: Manual override enabled.
options.overview: After single button push the relay turns on and automatically turns off after specified time. Another button push turns the relay off immediately

parameters.label: Auto off for relay 1
parameters.description: Time period for auto off, in miliseconds 0 - Auto off disabled

parameters.label: Auto off for relay 2
parameters.description: Time period for auto off, in miliseconds 0 - Auto off disabled

parameters.label: Sending commands to group 1 devices
parameters.overview:
Sending commands to control devices assigned to 1-st association group (key no. 1)
NOTE: Parameter 15 value must be set to 1 to work properly. This activates the double-click functionality - dimmer/roller shutter control

options.label: Commands are sent when device is turned on and off
Commands sent when device off with memorized state
options.overview:
commands are sent when device is turned off. Enabling device does not send control commands. Double-clicking key sends 'turn on' command, dimmers memorize the last saved state (e.g. 50% brightness).

NOTE: Parameter 15 value must be set to 1 to work properly. This activates the double-click functionality - dimmer/roller shutter control.

options.label: Commands are sent when device is turned off
options.overview: Enabling device does not send control commands. Double-clicking key sends 'turn on' command and dimmers are set to 100% brightness.

parameters.label: Sending commands to group 2 devices
parameters.overview:
Sending commands to control devices assigned to 2-nd association group (key no. 2).  

Info: Parameter 15 must be set to 1 to make this parameter work properly. This activates the double-click functionality - dimmer/roller shutter control.

options.label: Commands are sent when device is turned on and off
Commands sent when device off with memorized state
options.overview: Enabling device does not send control commands. Double-clicking key sends 'turn on' command, dimmers memorize the last saved state (e.g. 50% brightness).

options.label: Commands are sent when device is turned off
options.overview: Enabling device does not send control commands. Double-clicking key sends 'turn on' command and dimmers are set to 100% brightness.

parameters.label: Assigns bistable key status to the device status
parameters.description: Assigns bistable key status to the device status
parameters.overview: Info: Remote control from Fibaro System Is Still Possible. This function is useful When you want display status of external devices, e.g. Motion Sensor, in Fibaro System.

options.label: On/Off device changes status on key status change
Device status depends on key status
options.overview: Device status depends on key status: ON when the key is ON, OFF when the key is OFF.

parameters.label: Switch type connector
parameters.description: Switch type connector, you may choose between momentary and toggle switches

parameters.label: Operation of the Dimmer/Roller Shutter Controller

parameters.overview: Operation of the Dimmer and Roller Shutter Controller - enabling this option allows the user to dim lighting/shut roller by associating dimmer/Roller Shutter Controller and holding or double press of double switch (only mono-stable switch).

options.label: Dimmer/Roller Shutter Controller control is active
